                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_low_nox_regime",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream `MethaneOxidation: Low NOx Regime` testitem (test_methane_oxidation.jl:323-345). With HO₂ raised to 2.0e14 and NOx cut to NO=1.0e13, NO₂=1.0e14, the methylperoxy radical's chain-terminating fate R4 (CH₃O₂ + HO₂) overtakes its O₃-producing fate R3 (CH₃O₂ + NO) — upstream asserts R4 > R3. Reproduced structurally by pinning R4=103999999999.99998 > R3=7700000000.0 at rel=1e-10. R15 (the HO₂ + NO channel) and P_O3_gross are also pinned: in this low-NOx air mass gross ozone production collapses to 23900000000.0 m⁻³·s⁻¹, ~165× below the default-scenario value.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "HO2": 200000000000000.0,
                        "NO": 10000000000000.0,
                        "NO2": 100000000000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R3",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 7700000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R4",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 103999999999.99998
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R15",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 16200000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "P_O3_gross",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 23900000000.0
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_r1_doubles_when_oh_doubled",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream `MethaneOxidation: R1 Scales Linearly with OH` testitem (test_methane_oxidation.jl:414-439), which doubles OH via `remake` and asserts R1 doubles (ratio ≈ 2.0 at rtol=1e-6). With OH=2.0e12 (2× default) this test pins R1=570936008924.7509 — twice the default-scenario R1=285468004462.3754 to within one ULP. The OH-linearity is verified across all four OH-dependent reaction rates by also pinning R7, R8, R10 (each = k·CH₃OOH or HCHO·OH) and the diagnostic L_CH4 = R1 at their doubled values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "OH": 2000000000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R1",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 570936008924.7509
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R7",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 14086571470.696959
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R8",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3800000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R10",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 180000000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "L_CH4",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 570936008924.7509
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "r1_linear_in_methane",
                    "description": "Coverage beyond the upstream suite: R1 = k1·CH₄·OH is exactly linear in the methane concentration. With CH₄ doubled to 9.0e19, R1 and the methane-loss diagnostic L_CH4 both double to 570936008924.7509. Together with `upstream_r1_doubles_when_oh_doubled` this confirms R1 is bilinear in (CH₄, OH) and pins the L_CH4 = R1 identity under a CH₄ perturbation.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "CH4": 9e+19
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R1",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 570936008924.7509
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "L_CH4",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 570936008924.7509
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "peroxy_no_channels_linear_in_no",
                    "description": "Coverage beyond the upstream suite: both peroxy-radical + NO channels (R3 = k3·CH₃O₂·NO and R15 = k15·HO₂·NO) are exactly linear in NO, so the gross ozone production rate P_O3_gross = R15 + R3 is also linear in NO. With NO doubled to 5.0e15, R3, R15 and P_O3_gross all double (R3=3850000000000.0, R15=4050000000000.0, P_O3_gross=7900000000000.0). Establishes the NO-linearity that the `ch3o2_radical_fate_vs_no` example sweeps.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "NO": 5000000000000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R3",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3850000000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R15",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 4050000000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "P_O3_gross",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 7900000000000.0
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "methylperoxy_rates_scale_with_ch3o2",
                    "description": "Coverage beyond the upstream suite: the three methylperoxy-radical reaction rates scale differently with CH₃O₂ — R3 = k3·CH₃O₂·NO and R4 = k4·CH₃O₂·HO₂ are linear, while R5 = k5·CH₃O₂·CH₃O₂ is quadratic. With CH₃O₂ doubled to 2.0e14, R3 and R4 double (3850000000000.0 and 103999999999.99998) but R5 quadruples to 14000000000.000002. This pins the only quadratic-in-a-single-species rate in the mechanism and would catch a regression that linearized the CH₃O₂ self-reaction. P_O3_gross also moves (it inherits R3's CH₃O₂ dependence).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "CH3O2": 200000000000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R3",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3850000000000.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R4",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 103999999999.99998
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R5",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 14000000000.000002
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "P_O3_gross",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 5875000000000.0
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "termolecular_rates_linear_in_air_density",
                    "description": "Coverage beyond the upstream suite: the three termolecular reactions R2 (CH₃ + O₂ + M), R14 (H + O₂ + M) and R17 (O + O₂ + M) each carry the third-body factor M and are exactly linear in the air number density. With M doubled to 5.0e25, R2, R14 and R17 all double (R2=2.6250000000000005e18, R14=1496250000000000.2, R17=15750000000000.0). Confirms the cm⁶ → m⁶ termolecular rate-constant conversion and the M-linearity that distinguishes termolecular from bimolecular rates.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "M": 5e+25
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "R2",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.6250000000000005e+18
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R14",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1496250000000000.2
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "R17",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 15750000000000.0
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "hydroperoxide_rates_linear_in_ch3ooh",
                    "description": "Coverage beyond the upstream suite: all three methyl-hydroperoxide reactions — the photolysis R9 = j9·CH₃OOH and the two OH reactions R7 = k7·CH₃OOH·OH, R8 = k8·CH₃OOH·OH — are exactly linear in CH₃OOH. With CH₃OOH doubled to 2.0e15, R9, R7 and R8 all double (R9=10000000000.0, R7=14086571470.696959, R8=3800000000.0). Pins the photolysis-rate channel R9 against a regression that drops the j9 frequency or the CH₃OOH factor.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "CH3OOH": 2000000000000000.0
