                            "description": "R3 (CH₃O₂ + NO → CH₃O + NO₂) vs NO number density on a log x axis. A straight line through the origin — R3 = k3·CH₃O₂·NO is exactly linear in NO — the O₃-producing fate of the methylperoxy radical.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "NO",
                                "label": "NO number density (m^-3)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "R3",
                                "label": "R3, CH3O2+NO rate (m^-3 s^-1)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "r4_ch3o2_ho2_vs_no",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "R4 (CH₃O₂ + HO₂ → CH₃OOH + O₂) vs NO. A horizontal line — R4 = k4·CH₃O₂·HO₂ has no NO dependence — the chain-terminating fate of methylperoxy, which R3 overtakes as NO rises.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "NO",
                                "label": "NO number density (m^-3)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "R4",
                                "label": "R4, CH3O2+HO2 rate (m^-3 s^-1)"
