                    "id": "formaldehyde_loss_pathways_vs_oh",
                    "description": "How the branching of formaldehyde loss shifts with the hydroxyl radical concentration. OH is swept logarithmically from 1e11 to 1e13 m⁻³ with all other inputs at their defaults. HCHO has three loss channels: R10 (HCHO + OH) is the only one that depends on OH, while R11 and R12 (the radical and molecular photolysis channels) are fixed by the photolysis frequencies. As OH rises, R10 climbs linearly and the OH channel takes an increasing share of total HCHO loss — the branching-ratio behaviour discussed in the GasChem docs `Formaldehyde Branching Pathways` analysis.",
