                    "id": "gross_o3_production_no_ho2_heatmap",
                    "description": "Gross ozone production rate P_O3_gross = R15 + R3 as a joint function of NO and HO₂ (a 2-D log-log sweep). NO is swept from 2.5e14 to 2.5e17 m⁻³ and HO₂ from 1e13 to 1e15 m⁻³, with the other inputs at their defaults. P_O3_gross = NO·(k15·HO₂ + k3·CH₃O₂) is linear in NO and linear in HO₂ through the R15 channel: the heatmap surfaces how both the NOx supply and the HO₂ radical pool govern the methane mechanism's ozone output, with the high-NO / high-HO₂ corner the most productive.",
